Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for violation of the deadline and the procedure for paying for goods (works, services) when purchasing for state and municipal needs.
This law is designed to address the very acute problem of non-fulfillment of obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal purchases.
Two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not get paid for already executed state and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the Russian president instructed the General Prosecutor's Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem for special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who entered into unfunded contracts, tried in every possible way to evade payment commitments and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the whole country.
Since 2015, in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment for public orders, the prosecutor's office made 9.7 thousand submissions, 4,500 officials were brought to disciplinary responsibility, 533 were brought to disciplinary responsibility, 533 were brought to disciplinary account, 75 materials were submitted to investigative bodies for the organization of procedural inspections, 46 criminal cases were initiated.
As a result, more than 66 billion rubles in arrears to entrepreneurs were repaid.
And these huge sums accumulated far from the failure to pay multibillion-dollar contracts.
To the fabulous debts led numerous, systematic delays in paying services to entrepreneurs at a much more modest amount.
Here is a characteristic case.
The head of a small company won a tender for the provision of social transportation services for several million rubles.
The man invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled his obligations, but he did not receive the money in time.
The result is a growing financial com- pany of debts on wages, taxes, loans, which would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not seek help from the prosecutor's office.
Now in a number of regions the problem has been maximally leveled.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the aggregate amount of debt on state and municipal contracts, identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical levels, the prosecutor's office works in the mode of manual crisis management.
The Prosecutor-General personally conducts outreach meetings with representatives of the local authorities, who thoroughly examine all the violations discovered by prosecutors and measures for their immediate elimination.
Such operational meetings have already been held this year in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
The implementation of the Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of Administrative Offenses of the Russian Federation in the part of establishing administrative responsibility of the customer's officials for violating the deadline and the procedure for payment for goods (works, services) in procurement for government and municipal needs", which the Russian president signed last week, will improve qualitatively the payment discipline of public customers.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Prosecutor General's Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offenses with an article that provides for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 rubles for violation by the customer's official of the term and procedure for payment for goods, works and services for state and municipal purchases.
And if the official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offense, he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All the prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the application of these legislative innovations in practice.
Civil Rights Protection Group announced a travel alert in Missouri
The National Association for the Advancement of the Colored Population issued a warning for colored people traveling to Missouri, due to discriminatory state policies and attacks on racist grounds.
The group's statement reads: "The warning for travelers of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, valid until August 28, 2017, encourages African-American travelers, guests and citizens of Missouri to be particularly careful and to be extra careful when traveling around the state due to a number of dubious racist incidents that have recently occurred throughout the state and are listed here."
