PSG was fined 60 million euros (at the rate of 82 million dollars), which was later reduced to 20 million euros, and was ordered to limit the composition of his team in the "Champions League" during the season 2014-1015, 21 players instead of the usual 25.
UEFA monitors clubs that can try to outwit its financial inspections, inflating their income at the expense of companies associated with the owners of the club.
Although the Qatari company could sponsor PSG, but if the amount of financing was considered to be higher than the standard market rates, UEFA would not allow it to be considered a legitimate income.
This is exactly what happened in 2014, when UEFA decided that the amount of funding for "PSG" by the Qatari Tourism Authority was inflated.
