In Venice, tightened fines for tourists for inappropriate behavior
The Venetian authorities tightened fines for bathing in canals from 50 euros to 500 euros.
For walks around the city in a swimsuit or with a bare torso will now be fined 200 euros.
For 100 euros will be demanded from those who will arrange a picnic in a public place or ride a bike in pedestrian areas, TASS reports referring to the Association of Tour Operators of Russia.
In addition, it is mentioned that the authorities provide a fine for inscriptions on monuments of 400 euros and for garbage of 25 euros.
Inform tourists about the need to comply with the rules of conduct in Venice with the help of the special company "Enjoy, respect Venice" (#EnjoyRespectVenezia) in social networks, as well as through ads and posters on the city council website, on billboards and in the places where tourists gather most.
The campaign will be conducted in 10 languages.
According to the counselor for tourism of Venice Paola Mar, the information on the fines will be transferred to the embassies of the home countries of the violators, in order to warn their compatriots against such mistakes.
"The problem is that Venice is perceived as a beach," she noted.
In April, the administration of the Italian city announced plans to limit the flow of tourists.
In Venice, there is already a successful restriction on the number of tourists visiting the city center.
Instead of 100,000 people wishing to watch the Festa del Redentore festival, only 60,000 guests were admitted to the scene.
In addition, a moratorium has been introduced to create new hotels and fast food restaurants in the historic part of Venice.
