An experimental artist controls music and video with gestures - this is how leap motion technology works.
Only two stages of the festival will be performed by eight musical groups.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive zones and art objects, united by the idea of merging music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit a scientific buffet and watch the creation of cryomolding or quicksand sands from starch and water.
In the special zone of vinyl it will be possible to purchase plates of topical jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair there will be publications on various topics, including musical, popular science and biomedical literature.
