Electricity is cheaper for both residents and commodity producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) that lasted for more than a decade to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers are beginning to bear fruit.
Since September 1, the cost of low-voltage electricity for industrial customers has been reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country established indicative prices for electricity and capacity for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia in accordance with the Resolution of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Electricity and Capacity Market and the Consolidated Prognostic Balance Sheet of Production and Supply of Electric Power (Capacity) within the Unified Energy System of Russia for the Subjects of the Russian Federation" (dated July 17, 2017 No. 842).
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat commodity producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic have studded the thresholds of Moscow offices in vain attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power stations on the Angara flowing out of Lake Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
And only this year began moving.
In March, tariffs for electricity for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles / kWh to 3.93 rubles / kWh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the list of territories of price zones of the wholesale market, for which the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, the turn of industrial consumers has come.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of the Irkutsk region pays for kilowatt / hour 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least an approximate date for new tariff moves downward for Buryatia.
