In Russia, there will be two new territories for outstripping socio-economic development - Abaza and Novotroitsk.
The corresponding resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TORA in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city where 15 thousand people live, a special legal regime of business activity will operate, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
In the list of types of economic activities under which a special legal regime for business activities will operate in the Abaz TOR, for example, crop production, livestock production, production of food products, soft drinks and clothes are included.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the town-forming enterprise of LLC "Abakan mine".
In January 2017 the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development to create a TOP.
Similarly, the authorities of the Orenburg region have acted.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk also the territory of advanced social and economic development will be created.
This will allow diversifying the single-industry economy, reducing its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of Ural Steel, as well as creating more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attracting investments of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical supplies.
Novotroitsk became the first of the mono-cities of the Orenburg region, received the status of TOP.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOP are the following: profit tax of no more than 5% for the first five years, and at least 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential connection to various infrastructure facilities, and preferential rental rates.
